  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Creature Type.</strong> You are a Humanoid.<br /><br /><strong>Size.</strong> You are Medium or Small. You choose the size when you select this species.<br /><br /><strong>Speed.</strong> Your Speed is 30 feet.<br /><br /><strong>Darkvision.</strong> You have Darkvision to a range of 60 feet.<br /><br /><strong>Fire Resistance.</strong> You have Resistance to Fire damage.<br /><br /><strong>Reach to the Blaze.</strong> You know the @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.spells.Item.matSplProduceFla]{Produce Flame} cantrip. You can cast it as normal, and you can also cast it as a Bonus Action a number of times equal to your Proficiency Bonus, regaining all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest.</p><p>When you reach character level 3, you can cast the @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.spells.Item.matSplBurningHan]{Burning Hands} spell with this trait. When you reach character level 5, you can cast the @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.spells.Item.matSplFlameBlade]{Flame Blade} spell with this trait. Once you cast Burning Hands or Flame Blade with this trait, you cannot cast that spell with it again until you finish a Long Rest. You can also cast either of those spells using any spell slots you have of the appropriate level.</p><p>Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma is your spellcasting ability for these spells when you cast them with this trait (choose when you select this species). None of these spells require spell components when you cast them with this trait.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
